      • createSimulator

        public ComparchSimulator createSimulator(Capability capability,
                                         de.mdelab.morisia.comparch.Architecture eArchitecture,
                                         int runs,
                                         java.util.logging.Level logLevel,
                                         java.lang.String logFile,
                                         boolean logToConsole)
        Creates, if desired also configures, and returns an instance of the ComparchSimulator.
        Parameters:
        capability - the desired Capability that the simulator should support. According to this capability, the simulator will be configured with the required injectors and analyzers.
        eArchitecture - the Architecture element of the model (i.e., the root element of the model).
        runs - number of runs the simulator should run. One run is performed when invoking ComparchSimulator.injectIssues() which injects issues into the model. Issues injected by one run of the simulator should be handled by one run of the feedback loop.
        logLevel - the log level of the simulator.
        logFile - the name of the file that the logs will be stored. If this parameter is null, logging to a file is disabled.
        logToConsole - if true, logs are printed to the console, otherwise not.
        Returns:
        an instance of the ComparchSimulator configured by the given parameters.
